[{"id":"VR834489","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows, from left to right, a point charge, a labeled point P, and a sphere of radius r arranged in a line. The point charge has a charge of positive q and is a distance r from Point P. Point P is a distance r from the surface of the sphere, and the charge of the sphere is negative 2 q.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR834489.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A point charge and a solid insulating sphere of radius <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> are located near each other, as shown in the figure. The point charge has a positive charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q\"><math alttext=\"positive q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span>, and the sphere has a negative net charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 2 q\"><math alttext=\"negative 2 q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> uniformly distributed throughout its volume. What is the magnitude of the net electric field at Point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P\"><math alttext=\"P\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math></span></span>, which is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> from both the sphereâ€™s surface and the point charge?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR834489_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Zero</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"one half the fraction k q over r squared, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"one half the fraction k q over r squared, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"three halves the fraction k q over r squared, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"three halves the fraction k q over r squared, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 times the fraction k q over r squared, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"2 times the fraction k q over r squared, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mfrac><mrow><mi>k</mi><mi>q</mi></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]